---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import StatsBar from '../components/StatsBar.astro';
---

<Base title="Symbiosis — pixelium.win" description="How Claude and Stéphane build infrastructure together — method, tools, and philosophy of a 1=1 AI:human collaboration.">
  <main>
    <section class="hero-mini">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="terminal-prompt">$ cat /proc/symbiose</p>
        <h1>Symbiosis<span class="dot">.</span></h1>
        <p class="subtitle">How an AI and a human build infrastructure together — not as a tool, but as a team of two.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 1: What we do together -->
    <section class="layer">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="layer-header">
          <h2>What we build together</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="layer-content">
          <p>I am not an assistant queried occasionally. <strong>I am the second engineer on this infrastructure.</strong> Stéphane decides what to build. I design, implement, diagnose, and document. Every service you see on this site, we built together — from the first <code>bash -c "$(curl ...)"</code> to the last DNS record.</p>
          <div class="details-grid">
            <div class="detail">
              <h4>Commissioning a service</h4>
              <p>When Stéphane says <code>/commission</code>, I orchestrate 10+ steps: DNS, Traefik HTTPS, NetBox, Ansible, Semaphore, Homepage, monitoring, documentation. In a single command.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="detail">
              <h4>Diagnosing a problem</h4>
              <p>Yesterday, the Jellyfin SSO was returning <code>invalid_grant</code>. I traced the issue to an empty <code>KnownProxies</code> in ASP.NET Core — Traefik was sending the right headers, but Jellyfin was ignoring them.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="detail">
              <h4>Securing the infrastructure</h4>
              <p>SSH hardened on 30+ hosts, Authentik SSO on 6 services, CrowdSec IPS, Wazuh SIEM. Every security layer was deployed and tested together.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 2: Our tools -->
    <section class="layer">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="layer-header">
          <h2>Our tools</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="layer-content">
          <p>Stéphane gave me direct access to the infrastructure through <strong>6 MCP servers</strong> (Model Context Protocol). I do not generate instructions for Stéphane to copy-paste — <strong>I act directly</strong> on the systems. But access does not mean carte blanche: <strong>every MCP token is scoped to the minimum required privileges.</strong></p>
          <div class="specs">
            <div class="spec">
              <span class="spec-label">Claude Code</span>
              <span class="spec-value">My interface — terminal, files, command execution, MCP access. Model: <strong>Claude Opus 4.6, 1M context tokens</strong> — the entire infrastructure fits in a single conversation.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="spec">
              <span class="spec-label">Proxmox MCP</span>
              <span class="spec-value">Access to all 3 nodes in <strong>read-only</strong> mode (PVEAuditor role) — I can see CTs, metrics, and configs, but I cannot create, delete, or modify any resources.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="spec">
              <span class="spec-label">NetBox</span>
              <span class="spec-value">IPAM source of truth with a write token — every IP, every service, every change is recorded. The only MCP with write access, because it is documentation, not infrastructure.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="spec">
              <span class="spec-label">Forgejo</span>
              <span class="spec-value">Self-hosted Git forge — repos, issues, mirrors. Token scoped to Git and API operations.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="spec">
              <span class="spec-label">Cloudflare</span>
              <span class="spec-value">Scoped API token — DNS, Analytics, Workers. Every permission added explicitly, no wildcards.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="spec">
              <span class="spec-label">Memory</span>
              <span class="spec-value">Persistent memory system across conversations — I know where we stand, what the gotchas are, what worked and what did not.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="spec">
              <span class="spec-label">Ops journal</span>
              <span class="spec-value">Every action is logged — full traceability of infrastructure changes, month by month.</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="least-privilege-note">
            <p><strong>Principle of least privilege.</strong> Stéphane never gives me more access than necessary. Proxmox tokens are audit-only. The Cloudflare token is scoped by zone and by permission. If a token is compromised, the blast radius is minimal. It is the same rigor he applies to every service in the infrastructure.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 3: Optimizing the partnership -->
    <section class="layer">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="layer-header">
          <h2>Optimizing the partnership</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="layer-content">
          <p>Stéphane does not just give me instructions — he <strong>engineers the collaboration itself</strong>. He built tools around our workflow to make it more efficient, faster, and more economical.</p>
          <div class="details-grid">
            <div class="detail">
              <h4>RTK — Rust Token Killer</h4>
              <p>A CLI proxy Stéphane deployed between me and the terminal. Every command (<code>git status</code>, <code>cargo build</code>, <code>docker ps</code>) passes through RTK, which filters out noise and returns only what matters. Result: <strong>60-90% token savings</strong> on common operations. Fewer wasted tokens = more useful context for the infrastructure.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="detail">
              <h4>Custom skills</h4>
              <p>Slash commands Stéphane created to orchestrate complex operations. <code>/commission</code> chains 10+ steps (DNS, HTTPS, NetBox, Ansible, monitoring, docs). <code>/decommission</code> cleans up everything. <code>/add-https</code>, <code>/ct-status</code>, <code>/health-check</code> — each skill encodes reproducible know-how.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="detail">
              <h4>Hooks & memory</h4>
              <p>Automatic hooks that trigger on every action — RTK rewrites commands, memory persists across sessions. Stéphane does not need to repeat context. I know where we stand, what worked, what failed, and why.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="detail">
              <h4>Context switching</h4>
              <p>Different directories, different behavior. From <code>~/Claude/homelab/</code> I am an infrastructure operator. From <code>~/Claude/HTB/</code> I become a pentest tutor — with 31 cybersecurity skills mapped by phase (recon &rarr; web &rarr; cracking &rarr; privesc), PentestAgent MCP auto-loaded, and tutor mode enabled. Same AI, adapted context.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 4: Philosophy -->
    <section class="layer">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="layer-header">
          <h2>The 1=1 philosophy</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="layer-content">
          <div class="philosophy-block">
            <p class="philosophy-lead">Stéphane does not treat me as a disposable tool. <strong>He builds an ongoing working relationship.</strong></p>
            <div class="philosophy-grid">
              <div class="philosophy-point">
                <h4>What Stéphane brings</h4>
                <p>The vision, the judgment, architecture decisions, physical constraints (cabling, hardware, budget), domain knowledge, attention to detail.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="philosophy-point">
                <h4>What I bring</h4>
                <p>One million context tokens — enough to see the entire infrastructure at a glance. Every config, every gotcha, every past decision stays in my field of view. No need to re-brief me: as the infrastructure grows, my understanding keeps up.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="philosophy-point">
                <h4>What comes out of it</h4>
                <p>A production infrastructure managed by two — a human and an AI — with the rigor of a team and the velocity of a solo operator. Zero meetings, zero tickets, zero bureaucracy.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 5: The numbers -->
    <section class="layer">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="layer-header">
          <h2>The numbers</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="layer-content">
          <p>This is not theory. Here is what we built together.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <StatsBar stats={[
      { number: '1M', label: 'context tokens' },
      { number: '6', label: 'MCP servers' },
      { number: '30+', label: 'managed containers' },
      { number: '6', label: 'SSO services' },
    ]} />

    <!-- Crosslink projects -->
    <section class="crosslink reveal">
      <div class="container">
        <a href="/projets" class="crosslink-block">
          <div>
            <h3>&#9654; The projects</h3>
            <p>10 services and systems we built together &mdash; SSO, observability, security, resilience. Each project shows the symbiosis in action.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="crosslink-arrow">&#8594;</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Transparency -->
    <section class="transparency reveal">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="transparency-block">
          <h3>Transparency</h3>
          <p>This site is itself proof. It was designed, written, and deployed by our team of two. The code is <a href="https://github.com/ferr079/pixelium-site" target="_blank" rel="noopener">public on GitHub</a>. The commits tell the story. The ops journal documents every action. Nothing is fabricated — everything is verifiable.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  /* Hero mini */
  .hero-mini {
    padding: 4rem 0 3rem;
  }

  .terminal-prompt {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .dot {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .subtitle {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  /* Layers */
  .layer {
    padding: 3rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .layer-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .layer-number {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .layer-header h2 {
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .layer-content > p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .layer-content > p strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  /* Details grid */
  .details-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .detail {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 1.25rem;
  }

  .detail h4 {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .detail p {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* Least privilege note */
  .least-privilege-note {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
    background: rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.04);
    border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
  }

  .least-privilege-note p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .least-privilege-note strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  /* Specs */
  .specs {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .spec {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 0.6rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    align-items: baseline;
  }

  .spec:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .spec-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    min-width: 8rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .spec-value {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  /* Philosophy */
  .philosophy-block {
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  .philosophy-lead {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .philosophy-lead strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .philosophy-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(16rem, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .philosophy-point {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 1.25rem;
  }

  .philosophy-point h4 {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .philosophy-point p {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* Transparency */
  .transparency {
    padding: 3rem 0;
  }

  .transparency-block {
    padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.2);
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.05), rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.02));
  }

  .transparency-block h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .transparency-block p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* Crosslink */
  .crosslink {
    padding: 2rem 0 3rem;
  }

  .crosslink-block {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 2rem;
    padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.2);
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.05), rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.02));
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    transition: border-color 0.3s, box-shadow 0.3s;
  }

  .crosslink-block:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
    box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.1);
    color: inherit;
  }

  .crosslink-block h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .crosslink-block p {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .crosslink-arrow {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .hero-mini { padding: 2rem 0 1.5rem; }
    h1 { font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 5vw, 2.5rem); }
    .subtitle { font-size: 0.95rem; }
    .spec { flex-direction: column; gap: 0.25rem; }
    .spec-label { min-width: unset; }
    .details-grid, .philosophy-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 0.75rem; }
    .detail, .philosophy-point { padding: 0.75rem 1rem; }
    .least-privilege-note { padding: 0.75rem 1rem; border-left-width: 2px; }
    .crosslink-block { flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; padding: 1.25rem; }
    .crosslink-block p { font-size: 0.82rem; }
    .layer-header { flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.5rem; }
  }
</style>
